			Codes describing acceptable usage of a person or organisation's communication channel.
		</Intro>
		<ID>Communication Usage</ID>
		<Values>
			<Value>
				<Code>1</Code>
				<Text>Medical Incident</Text>
				<Description>Allows the school to decide which of a caregiver's communication channels is to be used
				when reporting a medical incident occuring to the learner.</Description>
			</Value>
			<Value>
				<Code>2</Code>
				<Text>SMS/TXT</Text>
				<Description>Allows the school to decide which of a caregiver's communication channels is to be used
				when sending an SMS (or TXT) message.</Description>
			</Value>
			<Value>
				<Code>3</Code>
				<Text>Unexplained Absence</Text>
				<Description>Allows the school to decide which of the caregiver's communication channels is to be used
				when reporting a learner's unexplained absence.</Description>
			</Value>
			<Value>
				<Code>4</Code>
				<Text>Intended Absence</Text>
				<Description>Allows the caregiver to decide which of the school's communication channels is to be used
				when notifying of a learner's intended absence.</Description>
			</Value>
		</Values>
